Fully voiced, beautiful visuals, great puzzles. This an awesome fully 3d point and click with a story. Loved it so much I bought the second one as soon as I finished this one. What happened to Zhero? I bought it, played it, and now it's no longer available on the play store.

"Return later in 2018 to continue your mission" It's 2020 now, and there has still been no update. Two years of nothing after that cliffhanger... unacceptable.

Incredible graphics, fun puzzles and intriguing story line. Since the game hasn't been updated in 2 years I'm wondering if the 5 levels are the end of it? It's like watching a movie that's missing the ending.

content: I enjoy puzzle games such as The Room (have all of them) and Da Vinci's house. So when Returner 77 came up as a suggestion, I opted to try. I find that I am not as engrossed by the game, especially because I find some of the puzzles to be too similar, in principle and kind, with slightly different solutions. Not only does this make the puzzles super easy, but also very monotonous. I have not finished the whole game yet; just don't have the desire to complete the same thing over and over again.
That was pretty short for $9. How disappointing.
Every bit as good as The Room. Worth every cent. So glad I found it.
Great animation and videos but gets incredibly boring.
This game brings you to a beautiful, immersive world of crystals, with alien, high-tech rooms of puzzles.

Let me start this by saying I don't do the sci-fi genre in games/films/anything at all. As a consequence I unwittingly scrolled past this game numerous times, which was my mistake. Loved the concept, cinematic beautiful visuals & overall quality feel. Lots of comparisons here to The Room, which I also love, but must get frustrating for the devs! For future games I'd like to see more variation in puzzles, longer levels & slightly less linear game play. Great start though, I'm off to buy Zhero.
Great
Great alien atmosphere and wonderful visual and sound design. Puzzles challenging but solvable. Maybe a little short and the ending is a little abrupt...

I often find myself uninstalling mobile games pretty fast, I can't stand those endless grinds and pay to advance game plays that most games use so I was surprised that I actually finished this one. It has a story and an end, a nice change and the puzzles are varied and challenging without being overly frustrating plus their is a hint system if you need it. One note, the game needs a connection to save, I played a few levels in a plane and has to redo them.
Repetitive puzzles, very boring

I really wish returner 77 was a longer game. Due to an amazing graphics, this why it is short. Game plot was pretty cool. You're in an alien atmosphere trying to free an other astronaut besides yourself. She gives hints too in a form a video log. Some of the puzzles are pretty hard. So unless you're the developer or a genius the hints really do help.

This is a beautiful game, wonderful graphics, great music, and engaging 
plot (so far - I haven't proceeded too far). For those who like puzzle 
games - you'll want to get this if you don't use Bluetooth headphones - or 
after they fix that bug. Why 2 stars, then if I'm providing a glowing 
review? Two things: * The audio studders consistently throughout the app, 
from app launch through game play. Audio buffering needs to be tweaked so 
that when it is played through Bluetooth headphones, it doesn't studder. 
This involves working around the limitations of Bluetooth audio. * The app 
asks for permission to access files on your device. Why is this needed? If 
there is a good reason for it, please call it out in your app description, 
and explain exactly why you need it. If possible, try to design your app 
without the need for that permission. I will be happy to amend my review 
with a higher star rating if any of these issues are addressed.
replyContent: Thanks for the honest review, and letting us know about the sound issue. We'll look into it :) Answering your second question: Returner 77 is a large game, and requires access to your device storage to safely read all game files and to save your game progress. For the game to function properly, we kindly ask you to grant the app this permission.
